The inscription has been erected by Aurelius Artemidorus on the tomb of his wife Amion: the usual spelling of this name is Ammion, and it is derived from Amma or Ma one of the names of Cybele. The deity whose priest Artemidorus was is unluckily not mentioned. Grammatical error-s like that in l. 12 are common in sepulchral inscriptions of this . country.

There remains the ancient city at Surmeneh: what name shall be given to it? lt was founded before the Roman or the Greek period, as is shown by some of the remains, especially the immense blocks of stone, twelve feet or more in length, with very simple mouldings such as could not belong to these periodS.
